A passenger train crashed into a minibus that was carrying workers to a factory in Turkey, killing 10 people and injuring five others, officials have said. 

Basri Guzeloglu, the local governor, said the train slammed into the bus today at a level crossing near the Mediterranean port city of Mersin. 

